# Intentionally empty.
# The OpenWrt kmod-mt76 umbrella package ships /etc/modules.d/mt76x2
# containing "mt76x2e", which triggers loading of mt76x2e +
# mt76x2_common + mt76x02_lib at boot. On MT7628 2.4G-only hardware
# (GL-MT300N-V2 etc.) there is no 5 GHz radio for those drivers to
# bind to; empirically they cause sporadic STA disconnects on the
# 2.4G radio (investigation 2026-04-21, TV-box 12:3e:ad:ac:66:d2
# dropping every 30–120 min).
#
# This overlay file wins over /rom/etc/modules.d/mt76x2 — empty
# content means no module is auto-loaded, mt7603e still loads via
# the mt7603e entry under a different file and handles the 2.4G radio.
